<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774246>
    dc:description "FIGURE 36. Pseudomontanococcus martini Kozár & Konczné Benedicty. Apterous adult male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=cranial apophysis, D=fleshy setae, E=hair-like setae, R=dermal reticulations on ocular sclerite and X=pores on head." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774246/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774236>
    dc:description "FIGURE 31. Cystococcus echiniformis Fuller. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=bifurcated fleshy setae on antenna, D=fleshy setae on leg and abdomen, E=hair-like seta on antennae, G=dermal markings, N=side view of simple eye, and iii–viii=abdominal segmentation," ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774236/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774252>
    dc:description "FIGURE 39. Tanyscelis verrucula (Froggatt). Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=cranial apophysis and X=pores on head." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774252/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774226>
    dc:description "FIGURE 26. Callococcus leptospermi (Maskell). Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=cranial apophysis and D=fleshy seta." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774226/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774254>
    dc:description "FIGURE 40. Tectococcus ovatus Hempel. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where X=pores on head." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774254/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 27. Calycicoccus merwei Brain. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). For abbreviations, see p. 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774248>
    dc:description "FIGURE 37. Pseudotectococcus rolliniae Hodgson & Gonçalves. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group).Where A=cranial apophysis, B=dorsal and ventral view of posterior abdominal segments and penial sheath, C=simple pore, D=fleshy seta, E=apical four segments of antenna and F=tibia and tarsus of metathoracic leg. For abbreviations, see p. 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774248/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774240>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33. Eriogallococcus isaias Hodgson & Magalhães. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=cranial apophysis, C=hair-like seta, D=fleshy seta, E=apex of style and F=tibia and tarsus of metathoracic leg. For abbreviations, see p. 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774240/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774238>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Dromedaricoccus hansoni Hodgson & Miller. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=cranial apophysis, B=side view of aedeagus, C=hair-like seta, D=fleshy seta and F=tibia and tarsus of metathoracic leg. For abbreviations, see p. 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774238/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774230>
    dc:description "FIGURE 28. Capulinia sallei Signoret. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where E=hair-like setae. For abbreviations, see p. 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774230/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774242>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34. Lachnodius?eucalypti (Maskell). Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=cranial apophysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774242/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774234>
    dc:description "FIGURE 30. Choneochiton casuarinae Hodgson, Mille & Cazères. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where A=hair-like setae, B=fleshy seta, C=proximal end of metathoracic leg, D=dorsal view of penial sheath, E=ventral view of penial sheath, and F=ventral view of anterior end of head." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774234/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774232>
    dc:description "FIGURE 29. Carpochloroides viridis Cockerell. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group). Where C=fleshy seta, D=hair-like seta and K=tibia and tarsus of metathoracic leg. For abbreviations, see p. 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774232/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774244>
    dc:description "FIGURE 35. Lobimargo williamsi Hardy & Gullan. Macropterous adult male (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group) (after Hardy et al. 2011). For abbreviations, see p. 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774244/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774250>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38. Stibococcus cerinus Miller & González. Macropterous male. (Eriococcidae, Gondwanan group) (after Miller & Gonzalez, 1975). Where C=loculate pores of glandular pouch and X=pores on head." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3774250/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

